          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An internal rate card is the accounting bridge between external provider invoices and internal team budgets. It applies a transparent markup schedule that recovers shared platform costs, introduces service tiers with explicit premiums and discounts, and versions every change with an effective date for accurate historical reporting. Building the rate card as code \u2014 rather than a spreadsheet \u2014 enables automated impact analysis, a deterministic charge computation at call time, and a reliable audit trail when teams question their bills."
          }
